The paper deals with object detection in geospatial imagery using machine learning techniques. Specifically, it focuses on building detection using low quality RGB-only imagery. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of machine learning algorithms for classification further supports this categorization. Other likely sub-categories include machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), graphics (cs.GR), and information retrieval (cs.IR), as these fields are closely related to computer vision and image processing.
